        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 1:52AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 151 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles northwest of Driscoll to Riviera.
Movement was southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kingsville, Bishop, Riviera Beach, Riviera, Ricardo, Kingsville Naval
Air Station, and Loyola Beach.

This includes US Highway 77 between mile markers 682 and 708.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
